Package: STREAMS
Title: Semi-supervised Trajectory REconstruction Across interval-censored Multi-State models
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Alessandra", "Pescina", , "pescina.alessandra@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: STREAMS is an R package for end-to-end estimation of progressive illness–death multi-state models from longitudinal visit-level data with partially observed disease onset. The pipeline trains a conditional variational autoencoder (CVAE) with a mean-teacher consistency constraint to model onset probability and onset-age uncertainty at patient-level. Model predictions are used to generate multiple imputed complete trajectories, fit parametric multi-state survival models, and pool transition-specific estimates using Rubin’s rules. STREAMS provides utilities for reproducible execution, diagnostics, and pooled model summaries.
